inn1.comm: bit of swing into Amla from middle stump, he helps it to midwicket
bit straighter now with less movement, Amla defends it back
moves it away this time from outside off with the angle, left alone
length delivery outside the off stump, Amla defends it into the covers
slightly wayward line on the pads, Amla tucks it away from outside leg to the midwicket boundary off the back foot for four
goes back to outside off on good length, Amla lets it go
142kph, on the pads to Amla again, this time from Milne, Amla chips it in the air well over midwicket with his wrists for another well-timed four

he's got him, easy catch for third man! There was room outside off and shaping away a bit, Amla threw his bat at it without reaching towards the ball, no footwork, and gets a thick top edge to Elliott

welcomes him with the short ball, RR takes it on the chest, he's rubbing it! It was short and on the stumps line, RR did well to drop his hands to get the bat out of the way, but the ball did enough to get him on the chest
dropped, but a very tough return catch. RR drove the low full toss firmly back to the bowler, Milne got both hands to it to his right, but it just didn't stick in
pushes the length delivery into the overs with a bottom edge and calls for a quick single
swings it in towards the off stump, RR pushes it back with a straight bat
swing and a miss for the wider delivery. Wheeler went wider outside off, it swung a bit too, RR chased and missed
closer to the batsman, it's fuller too and he drives it towards mid-off
shuffles across a bit for the short ball outside off and smashes it with a pull wide of midwicket for four
angled in towards the stumps, RR stays back and defends it back
on length outside off, RR reaches out a bit and pushes it to extra cover
short again to van Wyk, he stays back and pulls to fine leg
back of length with some room outside off, RR cuts it to extra cover uppishly
nicely done from RR, got a full delivery, the mid-off was wide and he merely pushed it down the ground using the pace of the ball to get four
inside edges the length delivery from outside off to fine leg for one
leans forward towards the ball outside off and defends into the covers

not RR, but van Wyk chops it onto the stumps! It was not too far from the off stump, van Wyk looked to cut it towards point or third man and only got an inside edge to the bottom of off stump. Both openers gone
some room outside off without much movement, he pushes into the covers
much fuller outside off, RR drives it nicely but straight to short cover
pitches on good length this time on the stumps, pushed down to mid-on off the back foot
full and swinging in towards off, pushed back to the bowler with a straight bat
on length this time on off stump, he pushes on the off side again
more towards middle stump now, RR stays back and pushes it down to mid-on. That's a maiden
on the toes on the back foot and works the back of length ball to fine leg to get off the mark
not much room outside off, but he waits for the ball and steers it just past a diving point fielder for two. Good running, there
just back of length on off stump, defends it towards cover off the back foot
some room outside off and he chops it to third man for one
144.6kph, stays back in the crease and helps it to long leg from middle and leg for one more. Getting good bounce, Milne
too short, it's around off and RR does well to stay back and pull it along the ground, wide of midwicket for four
four for AB too. Got width outside off, it was full as well and he went down on a knee to square-drive that wide of backward point
errs down the leg side now for a wide past the pads
just back of length on off with the angle, he helps it to point
bit too full on the stumps, pushed down with a straight bat to mid-on
angling in from outside off, AB comes down and pushes the ball into the covers
stays in the crease to cover the off stump and defends into the covers
in the air, wide of extra cover! AB closed the face of the bat to work it to leg, but was early into the shot and the leading edge was in the air for a bit but wide of the fielder
back of a length, cramps him as it comes in a bit to off, is tapped square on the off side
shortish into the pad, he does not have the room to swing freely but manages to send it down to deep backward square leg
drives this length ball nicely on the up, mid off runs to his left and slides to stop that
punches a short of a length ball with the slight inward angle to mid on
tight, very tight, AB takes on short midwicket with a nudge, he is playing from deep in the crease and even as he races down the pitch, he was gone had the lob from the diving fielder hit
turns a fullish ball off the pad past short midwicket, mid on fields
pitched up around 137 kph right on middle stump line, it straightens late on the left hander, and as he pushes half forward with caution, a thick edge runs behind point
well done, softly pushes a good length ball on off behind square, fielder charges in from backward point, but AB is in control of this single
played out from off towards midwicket
leans forward and drives a full delivery straight to widish mid off
not a drive, kind of a wristy whip from well outside off, and the ball races to the right of a diving mid on, not sure he was eyeing that region
floated up widish, he goes after it, mishits to covers
goes after another widish length delivery, closes the face on the drive and mishits it once more
stays half forward and tries to tap a length ball behind square, point is around
good drive as AB times it with a straight, firm followthrough, finds the bowler
wants to go down the ground again, but this is angled in from wider of the crease and he mistimes it off the inner part of the bat
short of a good length, he opens the face and runs it to third man
tossed up widish, he waits for it to turn and cuts to cover
punches with the turn to the left of cover
shortish ball coming in to the pad, he tries to rock back but it is on to him before he can get in a position to pull, knocks it back to the bowler
straightening on middle stump, he goes back to defend
fullish on leg stump line, and he bends on his knee to paddle it towards fine leg
steps out, works a flighted one with the spin past square leg
length delivery angled on middle and leg, pushed down the track
bat face closes as he tries to force a drive to a length ball slanted across, takes the single as the ball goes towards mid off
good length ball, just outside off, a thick inside edge takes it through square leg
Sodhi dives at mid off to stop this push, he is off balance as he throws it at the non-striker's end, and misses with a weak throw, AB was a long way out attempting the single
driven to extra cover off the front foot
whipped off the pad to deep backward square leg
some flight on the off stump and RR sweeps it with the turn to deep midwicket
beats him! Beautifully bowled on off stump, nice flight to draw AB forward for a push and the turn beats him
early call for one from AB after he tucks the shorter ball to backward square leg
comes down a step and pushes the full ball back to Sodhi
on the off stump now, not as much flight, and RR cuts it to backward point for one
in the air for a bit, bounces a couple of times before cover. It was on the leg side and RR closed the face of the bat early, leading edge went safely towards cover
length delivery right on middle stump now, RR brings his bat down to defend it solidly on the off side for one
length delivery towards the stumps, AB defends off the back foot
some room outside off, back of length too and he guides it to third man for one
charges down to make it a low full toss and he drives that nicely down the ground, to just clear a diving mid-off for four
fullish on the stumps again, he pushes it down towards mid-off for one
nicely flighted on the stumps, RR blocks it back
shorter and flatter, this one's going away and keeps low too, RR pushes to cover
leans forward into it and tucks the ball from outside off with the wrists to wide long-on. Sent back for the second
bit of flight on leg stump, pushed back to the bowler
comes down the track and steers the low full toss from leg to long-on for one
takes a step down for the back of length ball turning in, pushed past Sodhi for one

he's given it away, chips the ball to mid-off! Rossouw cleared his front foot to clear mid-off, played the shot with a big follow through, off the fullish ball, but it wasn't timed properly and Williamson took it easily to his right
angles it in towards off stump, keeps a tad low and Miller defends off the back foot
angles it in again, fuller on off and Miller steers it to mid-on
solid forward defence for the length delivery outside off
back of length now, still now room as Miller stays back and helps it to midwicket
length delivery again on the off stump, tucked to midwicket with the angle
comes down to take it on the full but the ball drifts in and he defends softly to midwicket
touch shorter on the leg stump, worked away behind square on leg for one
turns away from middle towards off, AB makes room and pushes it wide of cover
some room for Miller too, he slices it towards backward point. Oh, a fumble there gives them two
shorter ball now and turning in, easily pulled by Miller to deep midwicket
full and flighted on middle, driven with the turn to cover for one
hardly any room outside off, from back of length and AB defends off the back foot to point. Sent back by Miller
some width now and fullish outside off, but driven straight to cover
bit of width and back of length, he tucks it late to third man

another one caught, Bracewell gets Miller too! It was towards the pads on length, Miller closed the face of the bat early and the leading edge flew to the off side. Munro, at short cover, jumped up just in time to grab it with both hands
driven uppishly, misfield at extra cover and it goes for four! It bounced a couple of times before the fielder but it went through his legs to give Behardien four easy runs
in the block hole outside off, Behardien blocks off the back foot
plenty of flight outside off, he reaches out and drives to backward point
shouts of catch it as AB sweeps against the turn for a top edge, but it goes wide of short fine leg for two in the gap
makes some room and pushes the ball off the back foot into the covers
drifting in a bit, full and flighted just outside off and it's mistimed back to Sodhi
defends the similar delivery on the front foot off the middle this time
bit of room outside off, he cuts off the back foot to backward point
no room on off stump, length delivery is pushed on the off side
touch fuller outside off, driven straight to cover now
angled in towards middle and leg now, steered down to mid-on
almost in the block hole towards the off stump, sent back to the bowler
slightly back of length on off, he defends it into the covers
slightly fuller outside off, he drives it just past cover for one
way too short, he rocks back and slams that with a powerful pull to the midwicket boundary for four
not as short now, but he almost scoops that one from middle stump to the midwicket boundary for four more
good turn outside off now, he lets it go
outside the off stump, steered with the turn to deep cover for one
nicely driven off the front foot into the covers for one more
pretty wide outside off, turns away further and he leaves it alone
towards the pads and he glances it fine off the pads for two
much straighter and he pushes it down with a straight bat to long-on
110kph, slower offcutter on the stumps, pushed down to long-on again
slightly outside off, driven off the front foot to cover
stay back to punch the ball from outside off to long-on to bring up the team's 100
some room outside off, driven off the back foot to deep cover and he retains strike
slowish outside off, steered wide of cover for one
full and on middle and leg, pushed down to long-off for one
well outside leg with some turn, he went back and defended it to mid-on
fuller on middle, tucked towards the midwicket region for one
drifting in towards leg stump, it's pretty full and AB drives it down to long-off
width outside off, he reaches out and swishes at it to find deep cover
length delivery on the off stump, pushed to midwicket
slower and shorter on off stump, gives him enough time to go back and tuck it to leg
seams it in a bit towards middle, steered straight to midwicket

that's the big one, AB gone too! Scrambled seam on back of length around off, he waited for it but it bounced a bit extra and nipped in a tad. He looked to steer it to leg but just checked his shot to give a simple catch to Guptill at midwicket
punches the back of length ball into the covers
solid forward defence for the length delivery outside off
pushes the delivery from outside off to deep cover for one
slightly back of length on off, defends off the back foot
looks to tuck it to leg but the back of length ball beats him
can't get bat on it again as the ball angles in, but gets a leg bye
coming in towards middle stump, tucked off the back foot to deep midwicket for two
towards the stumps, he defends it back off the back foot
straight delivery, rolled his fingers over it and he pushes it down the ground for one
makes some room and drives the full toss straight to cover
another loopy slower one outside off, pushed towards cover point for one
just back of length on middle, finds short midwicket
defends it off the front foot now from outside off to the covers
pretty straight delivery on off stump, he defends it back
some width outside off, pushes it wide of point off the back foot for one
steers the ball from off stump straight to point
defends another length delivery into the covers
gets some room but can't clear point with a back-foot punch
angled in now and it's tucked to mid-on for one
angled in towards the pads, steered to deep midwicket for one
back of length on off, he defends it to cover
pretty full on off stump, he drives it straight to mid-off
some width outside off, not much, and it's driven into the covers
tight again outside off, pushed to cover again
fullish now on the stumps, Behardien pushes it back to the bowlers. Just one from the over
pushes the length delivery down to long-on for one
on middle and leg now, steered straight to midwicket
thick edge goes just past the keeper to short third man for one
back of length outside off, punches it off the back foot to deep cover
slow yorker on the middle stump, he blocks it back
little bit of room outside off, steered towards deep point and they come back for two
solid forward defence for the length ball to point
offcutter towards middle stump, he guides it late to third man for one
on the pads, he clips it wide of deep midwicket in the gap for two
153.7kph, in the block hole on off stump. That was fast and Behardien blocked it back
doesn't bounce as much as he expected, he pulled and missed as the ball struck him on the back thigh pad

pushes the back of length ball with soft hands from off stump to mid-off, gets a quick single. But there's a direct hit from KW at the bowler's end and they have gone to the third umpire. Behardien in safely
length delivery on the stumps, pushed down to silly mid-on
some room outside the off stump, steered towards deep cover for one
errs down the leg side, it deflects off the pad fine on the leg side for two leg byes
length delivery pushed down the ground, it bisects Elliott and Guptill at silly mid-on
delicately deflects the ball off the pads fine on the leg side
driven firmly down the ground, it was pretty full and deepish mid-off got a hand to it. Then long-on ran around to cut it in
back of length on the off stump, he defends it back
149.9kph, loud appeal for lbw turned down! Swings it in towards the stumps, Behardien shuffled across to work it to leg, he missed and was struck just outside off
dropped, but too tough again! The batsman punched it back to the bowler with some power, it was around his right shoulder but too quick and it popped out towards mid-on
outside the off stump, punches it straight to cover
149kph, on length on the off stump, he defends as there's no room at all
some turn on middle stump, he defends it back

he strikes, traps Wiese right in front of leg stump and the umpire took his time but the finger went up eventually. It was flattish from length, beat Wiese's sweep. But it might have pitched outside leg, that's what delayed the deicsion. Yes, replays show it pitched marginally outside leg
some turn for the length ball outside off, it's pushed to cover
wider outside off, cuts it to point off the back foot
steers the ball with the turn from outside off to long-off
flatter outside off, keeps a bit low as it's defended off the back foot
angled towards the pads, it's worked to fine leg for one
back of length and towards off stump, he defends it back
length delivery on the stumps now, thick inside edge goes to deep midwicket for one
more towards the leg stump, flicked to deep midwicket for one more
defends the length delivery from outside off to the off side
fuller on the pads now, clipped away in the gap wide of deep midwicket for two
flighted outside off, driven with the turn to long-off for one
edged fine, just past slip and goes for four! He went to the back foot to allow the ball to turn, poked his bat and got a thick just wide of first slip
pushes the fuller delivery down to mid-off
presses forward and defends the length ball into the covers
outside off, pushed to cover again with the turn
short and flat on the leg side, pulled to long leg for one
guides the back of length ball to third man for one
fullish on middle and leg, pushed down to mid-on
defends the length delivery with the angle to midwicket
offers a straight bat defence for the length ball to mid-on
presses forward to defend the ball to cover now
slower one on 125kph, middle-stump line and it's clipped to deep midwicket for one
on the off stump now, tucked off the back foot to leg for one
some turn for the length delivery as it's turned down to mid-on for one
flight, drift and full on middle, driven down to long-off for one
way too short and it's hammered to the midwicket boundary for a powerful six, brings up his fifty
presses forward and defends the ball to off side
full and wide outside off, steered with the turn to extra cover
back of length on the stumps, worked towards fine leg for one
stays back and defends the ball to leg
touch back of length around off and it's pushed down to mid-on
fullish on the pads, clipped straight to midwicket
solid defence for the length ball on off, just two from the over
steers the ball with the turn to extra cover from length
too full on the off side, he slams it down the ground, just wide of mid-on for a powerful slog
full and wide outside off, shuffles across and drives it to extra cover for one
on length on the pads, clipped off the back foot to leg
reverse sweeps that with the turn from outside off, it was flat already, and Bracewell chases to the boundary with a slide but can't keep it in
presses forward and turns it from outside off to leg for one
angling in from back of length, pushed down to mid-on
touch shorter and coming in again, helped to midwicket
fuller now on the pads, but clipped straight to midwicket again
makes some room, the ball chases him too and he can't clear midwicket again
almost a yorker on leg, pushed down to long-on for one
back of length on the off stump, he defends as there's no room and just one from the over
pretty wide outside off, steered into the covers for one
tries to cut off the back foot, pace was taken off the ball and he missed
on length outside off, pushed down to mid-off now
on the leg stump now, clipped to deep square leg for one
pushes the length ball down to silly mid-on
goes back in the crease and helps the incoming ball to midwicket for one more
short of a length delivery chopped to the right of third man for a couple
drives a pitched up delivery out to the sweeper
length ball on the line of off, he opens up half forward and plays it out towards cover
goes for the blockhole, does not quite get it right up there, Philander turns it to short midwicket
slowish short of a length ball tucking him up with the incoming angle, tapped to short cover
gets forward to a length ball and drives, but without power, and straight to cover
length delivery pushed to the left of the bowler, who dives to stop it
has a go at a widish one but hits it straight to the man at extra cover
slower length ball coming in to off, pushed off the front foot to extra cover
gets bat around pad to turn this in front of square, but midwicket denies them the single
no pace to work with, not much width too, and he taps it to extra cover
slight room this time but no pace again and he opens the face to guide it to the sweeper
slowish short ball, he drags the pull past short midwicket for a couple
pitched up, around middle and leg, turned to midwicket
reaches forward and pushes on the up, cannot squeeze it past cover
glides it against the incoming angle to third man
he was making some room when this came around off as a low full toss, he works it through midwicket
back of a length delivery turned to midwicket
full on off, hint of late swing and it's driven down straight to mid-off
145.6kmh, swinging in to middle and leg, pushed down to long-on for one
drives, but mistimes the fullish delivery into the covers for one
leans forward a bit and drives this to cover now
big swing and a miss! There was some width outside off, he unleashed an extravagant drive and missed
146.4kmh, no room this time, right on off stump and it's pushed back. Milne gets a hand to it to save a few runs
121.3kph, slower ball and it's mistimed high on the off side to mid-off. It was pitched up, looked like an offcutter, Behardien drove it down the ground and got an edge for an easy catch to mid-off
on the off side, back of length, worked to the leg side for two
fuller on the off stump, helped to the leg side
in the block hole on off stump, pushed to midwicket this time
half-volley on the off stump now, driven down to long-on for one

mix up and that's an easy run out at the keeper's end! Phangiso took off for the run after pushing the ball towards point with soft hands, but he was halfway down by the time Big Vern said no and Phangiso turned around. Guptill picked the ball and threw it easily to Ronchi to take the bails off
145.8kph, swinging and in the block hole outside off, pushed to the off side
150.6kph, targets the stumps now, Steyn defends it back somehow
full and outside off, Steyn swings and misses with a big drive
bit of room, not much, and it's driven square to point
finds the gap with a thick edge now, got the drive out again and the ball went between backward point and third man for two
tries the yorker, it's a low full toss on off and pushed down to long-on for one
straight bat push for the length ball on the stumps and Bracewell gets a hand to it to save at least one
makes room this time, but it's a back of length ball and Steyn defends it back
makes room again, it's a full toss too but his drive can't clear the cover fielder. Another dot

another run out! Steyn charged down the ground to slam the full delivery to cover, the fielder ran in from the edge of the circle and got a direct hit at the non-striker's end. Steyn lost his bat while dragging it in and he knows he's out. Latham was the fielder
full on off stump, driven down to long-on for one
slogs the length ball to deep midwicket for one
in the block hole around off, pushed gently to point
makes room, it's a full delivery with some swing on the middle stump and it's driven nicely to deep cover in the gap for two
138kph, mixes it up with the short ball around off, Tahir tries to guide to third man but misses
146.5kph, outside off now with some room, Tahir swings and misses
drives the attempted yorker uppishly and straight to deep cover. Retains strike for the last over
slower ball, back of length on the off stump, Tahir goes on his toes and guides it to third man
inside edge off the slog is rolling away to the fine-leg boundary and Milne dives at the boundary to save one

it's over, another run out and SA all out for 204. Tahir took off for the single after pushing the ball towards point, Philander sent another batsman back, late on the call, and Guptill ran to the stumps with the ball in his hands and did the rest

inn2.comm: gentle good length ball with slight away shape outside off, left alone
short of a length, slight inward angle, tucked behind square
128.8 kph back of a length on the left-hander's pad, turned to square leg
goes back in the crease, moves across to off and chops this length ball past a diving slip
short of a length again, just outside off, tapped to point
pitches it further up, tight line close to off, it is left alone, and bounces well in front of the keeper
shortish, spinning in from outside off, turned to square leg
tries to sweep and is hit on the pad, but well outside the line of off stump
punches this cautiously down the ground, waits till it passes the bowler and takes the single to long on
has him reaching forward for a drive, but he ends up hitting it to the bowler
gets forward to defend to extra cover
gets something out of the cover as he chops this shortish one to the deep point boundary
short of a good length, close to off stump, Latham taps it away off the back foot
good lines from Philander, around that off stump region, good length, defended
stands outside the crease on off and leans forward to defend
batting outside the crease and on off again, and pushes a length ball to the bowler
sends it on to the pads, and Latham flicks in the air, over a leaping fielder at midwicket
tightens up with a good length delivery on middle, which is played out to the leg side
angles it in too much and slants it down the leg side
tossed up full and Guptill attacks it, slogs it from just outside off, hasn't middled it, but dragged it past mid on off the inside part of the bat
pushed off the front foot to extra cover
Guptill attacking the left-arm spinner again, fetching it from well outside off this time, and sweeping in front of square
dropped, Phangiso had the opportunity to hit back after those boundaries, as Guptill leaned forward and spooned a drive back to him, he tumbled to his left, but could not hold on
Guptill is not holding back, overpitched from Phangiso around off and he has mowed it straight and high
leans forward to defend to the off side
begins just short of a driving length outside off, he walks into a forward defensive but is not getting the single
comes on slowly, leg-sidish, and is turned square for a single
gets the bat around his front pad in time as Philander angles it in, gets some inward movement, Guptill pushes it towards mid on
big gap between bat and pad as he is late in getting forward to this length ball outside off, defends off a thick inside edge
steps across and taps a length ball in the direction of midwicket
short of a good length, jabbed away square
speeds in and hurls it 137 kph on a length, across the left-hander, who totally mistimes the drive, the ball rolls on to the pitch
this time he times the shot, not overhitting, not much more than a firm  push on the up as he takes a step forward, the ball races past mid off
angles across far away from the left hander outside off
very full outside off, he crouches and opens the face to send it to third man
some inswing for Steyn but the angle is too sharp and this is another wide, down leg
gets the front foot out to this 140 kph length ball outside off, defends off a thick inside edge
short of a good length on the line of the stumps, he moves across and gets behind the line
stays on the crease to a widish length ball and tries to flay it past point, does not beat the fielder
good length just outside off, Latham is nicely forward to defend
turned in front of square on the leg side for a single
inches outside off as Philander continues to probe away, Guptill gathers himself into a defensive push
sees it pitched up, but is a touch late in getting forward and is not able to time the straight drive
short of a good length on the line of middle, softly pushed to short extra cover
another one on the line of off, Guptill defends quietly
starts on to the pad with fine leg up and is tucked away neatly behind square for four
gets the line right, just outside off, short of a length, he taps it behind square and they cross over for one
shortish, not much bounce on that, he tries to force it behind square on leg, mishits it weakly for a single
had some width on this length ball but he was moving across and mistimes it to extra cover
turned backward of square on the leg side

four more for New Zealand, Wiese strays on to the pads of the right hander now, and Guptill works him behind square, the man in the deep is well in front of square, and has no chance on this quick outfield
short of a length, couple of feet outside off, left alone
another boundary, not how Latham intended, goes for a big drive to a wide length ball and edges it along the ground, past lone slip, just past third man too
back of a length, on off stump, can't do much with that apart from getting behind the line to block
slight width, and Latham latches on to that instantly, cutting the shortish ball past point
139.2 kph short of a length ball without the width of the previous one, more zip too, he lets it be
comes forward as this one pitches on a good length, and runs it to point
pitched up, angled in, he leans into a drive, but there is long on in place
gets away with one on the pads as this is tucked to short fine leg
stays on the crease and nudges a good length ball to midwicket
Wiese overpitches and Guptill drives dead-straight, just past the stumps at the other end, long on has to run across and slide to stop it
walks across wanting to beat short fine leg, but turns this off the pad straight to the fielder
Guptill wants the second after Latham clips this length ball to deep midwicket but rightly turns back after taking quite a start
starts with one sliding across the left hander, who slaps it to the sweeper off the back foot
flighted googly, Guptill lunges forward and smothers it
tosses it up on to the pad, Guptill nudges to midwicket
on a length, and that allows him to whip it wide of long on for a well-run couple
full outside off and he drives hard, down to long off
flat delivery punched off the back foot to the right of the sweeper
angled in on a good length towards off, he leans forward to push it to long on
too full, and down the leg side, fine leg is in the deep though and keeps them to one
slow length ball outside off, he reaches forward to block
walks down the pitch after tapping this to the bowler's right, but Wiese goes sprawling to stop it
stays in the crease and tries to force a length ball away, extra cover cuts it off to his right
that was crunched on the up, and Miller has saved some runs with a dive at extra cover, there was a sweeper in the deep, but not sure he would have been able to stop that
back of a length ball guided to short third man
starting outside off and moving further away, he reaches for it, only manages to get as far as extra cover
short and wide, he gets hold of the cut, but has placed it straight to the sweeper
good length ball on middle stump line, defended
slanted in to the pads, nudged down to fine leg
has the width as Behardien bangs it in short outside off, but slaps it to point
